modules.description: Computes cryptographic hashes and HMACs, and performs symmetric encryption and decryption using a provided key. Operates on string inputs to produce hashed, signed, or encrypted string outputs. Used for securing message integrity, generating digests, and protecting sensitive data in transit.

Provides functions to generate, serialize, and validate macaroons, including adding and verifying caveats. Works with byte sequences and structured caveat data. Used to implement secure delegation tokens in authentication systems.

Creates and manipulates macaroons with location, identifier, and signature fields. Adds first-party and third-party caveats, binds discharge macaroons for verification, and serializes/deserializes macaroons for network transmission. Verifies caveats using a provided check function and associated discharge macaroons.
